 k тЙа 0` for `k` large enough (in fact, for `k > 0`). Then we have:\n   `sinh(r / k) / (r / k) тЖТ 1`, and multiplying by `r` gives `r (sinh(r / k)/(r / k)) тЖТ r`.\n\nBut perhaps in Lean, it is easier to avoid cases by using `tendsto_sinh_div_self`, because:\n\nWe have `k sinh(r / k) = r * (sinh(r / k)/(r / k))` if `r тЙа 0`. But to avoid cases, perhaps we can define a function that is `sinh(t)/t` when `t тЙа 0`, and `1` otherwise. \n\nBut perhaps it's not necessary.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps:\n\n`sinh(t)/t тЖТ 1` as `t тЖТ 0`, `t тЙа 0`.\n\nThus, for any sequence `t_k тЖТ 0` with `t_k тЙа 0`, we have `sinh(t_k)/t_k тЖТ 1`.\n\nIn our case, if `r тЙа 0`, take `t_k = r / k`. Then `t_k тЖТ 0`, `t_k тЙа 0`, and thus `sinh(t_k)/t_k тЖТ 1`.\n\nIf `r = 0`, we have `t_k = 0`, and `k sinh(0) тЖТ 0`.\n\nThus, perhaps:\n\nFor `r тЙа 0`, we have that `(r / k)` is a sequence `тЖТ 0`, `тЙа 0`, and then `sinh(r / k)/(r / k) тЖТ 1`, and then multiply by `r`. \n\nBut for `r = 0`, the result is trivial.\n\nIn Lean, it's perhaps better to start with `r тЙа 0`, and then do `r = 0` separately.\n\nAlternatively, perhaps use that `Real.tendsto_sinh_div_self` is `Tendsto (fun x => sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1)`, and then:\n\nFor `r тЙа 0`, `(r / k : тДЭ) тЖТ 0`, and for `k` large enough, `r / k тЙа 0`.\n\nSo `(r / k)` is eventually in `ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0 0`. Therefore, composing with `x тЖж sinh(x)/x`, we get `sinh(r / k)/(r / k) тЖТ 1`. Then multiply by `r`.\n\nBut in Lean, perhaps:\n\n```\nhave h : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => r / k) atTop (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0)\n```\n\nBut is that true? \n\n`r / k тЖТ 0`, and for `k > |r|`, `r / k тЙа 0`. So `r / k` is eventually in `ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0`.\n\nThen `(fun x => sinh x / x)` is `Tendsto (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1)`.\n\nThus, the composition gives that `(sinh(r / k)/(r / k)) тЖТ 1`.\n\nBut it requires a little work in Lean to say that `r / k` eventually in `ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0`.\n\nBut perhaps we can use:\n\n`(r / k)` tends to `0`, and `(r / k)` is eventually `тЙа 0",
      "\n  have hтВБ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n    have hтВВ : Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n      -- Prove that sinh(x)/x tends to 1 as x тЖТ 0\n      have hтВГ : HasDerivAt (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x) 1 0 := by\n        simpa using Real.hasDerivAt_sinh 0\n      have hтВД : HasDerivAt (fun x : тДЭ => (x : тДЭ)) 1 0 := by\n        simpa using (hasDerivAt_id (0 : тДЭ))\n      have hтВЕ : Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n        have hтВЖ : (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) = (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) := rfl\n        rw [hтВЖ]\n        convert HasDerivAt.tendsto_slope_zero hтВГ (hтВД) using 1 <;> simp [sub_eq_add_neg] <;> field_simp\n        <;> ring\n      exact hтВЕ\n    -- Use the known limit of sinh(x)/x as x тЖТ 0\n    have hтВГ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n      by_cases h : r = 0\n      ┬╖ -- If r = 0, the expression simplifies and we handle it separately\n        subst h\n        simp_all [div_eq_mul_inv]\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            simp_all [Filter.Tendsto]\n            <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Metric.ball, Real.dist_eq]\n                <;>\n                norm_num <;>\n                linarith\n              })\n          })\n        <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            simp_all [Filter.Tendsto]\n            <;>\n            (try\n              {\n                simp_all [Metric.ball, Real.dist_eq]\n                <;>\n                norm_num <;>\n                linarith\n              })\n          })\n      ┬╖ -- If r тЙа 0, we can directly use the known limit\n        have hтВД : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := by\n          have hтВЕ : ContinuousAt (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) 0 := by\n            have hтВЖ : ContinuousAt (fun k : тДЭ => (r : тДЭ) / k) 0 := by\n              apply ContinuousAt.div\n              ┬╖ exact continuousAt_const\n              ┬╖ exact continuousAt_id\n              ┬╖ norm_num\n            exact hтВЖ\n          have hтВЖ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := by\n            have hтВЗ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ (r / 0)) := by\n              apply Tendsto.mono_left _ nhdsWithin_le_nhds\n              have hтВИ : ContinuousAt (fun k : тДЭ => (r : тДЭ) / k) 0 := by\n                apply ContinuousAt.div\n                ┬╖ exact continuousAt_const\n                ┬╖ exact continuousAt_id\n                ┬╖ norm_num\n              have hтВЙ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r : тДЭ) / k) (ЁЭУЭ 0) (ЁЭУЭ (r / 0)) := by\n                have hтВБтВА : ContinuousAt (fun k : тДЭ => (r : тДЭ) / k) 0 := hтВИ\n                convert hтВБтВА.tendsto using 1 <;> simp\n                <;>\n                (try\n                  {\n                    simp_all [div_eq_mul_inv]\n                    <;>\n                    field_simp\n                    <;>\n                    ring\n                  })\n              simpa using hтВЙ\n            have hтВИ : r / (0 : тДЭ) = 0 := by simp\n            rw [hтВИ] at hтВЗ\n            exact hтВЗ\n          exact hтВЖ\n        -- Compose the limits to get the desired result\n        have hтВЕ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n          have hтВЖ : Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := hтВВ\n          have hтВЗ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := hтВД\n          have hтВИ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n            have hтВЙ : (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) = (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) тИШ (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) := by\n              funext k\n              <;> field_simp\n              <;> ring\n            rw [hтВЙ]\n            -- Compose the limits using the fact that sinh(x)/x tends to 1 as x тЖТ 0\n            have hтВБтВА : Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := hтВВ\n            have hтВБтВБ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := hтВД\n            have hтВБтВВ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := hтВД\n            have hтВБтВГ : (0 : тДЭ) тИИ ({0} : Set тДЭ) := by simp\n            have hтВБтВД : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := hтВД\n            have hтВБтВЕ : Filter.Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := hтВВ\n            have hтВБтВЖ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => Real.sinh (r / k) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := by\n              -- Use the fact that the composition of the limits is the limit of the composition\n              have hтВБтВЗ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) := by\n                have hтВБтВИ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 0) := hтВД\n                have hтВБтВЙ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) := by\n                  apply tendsto_nhdsWithin_of_tendsto_nhds\n                  -- Use the fact that the limit is 0 and 0 is in the closure of the punctured neighborhood\n                  <;> simp_all [h]\n                  <;>\n                  (try\n                    {\n                      simp_all [div_eq_mul_inv]\n                      <;>\n                      field_simp\n                      <;>\n                      ring\n                    })\n                  <;>\n                  (try\n                    {\n                      simp_all [Filter.Tendsto]\n                      <;>\n                      (try\n                        {\n                          simp_all [Metric.ball, Real.dist_eq]\n                          <;>\n                          norm_num <;>\n                          linarith\n                        })\n                    })\n                  <;>\n                  (try\n                    {\n                      simp_all [Filter.Tendsto]\n                      <;>\n                      (try\n                        {\n                          simp_all [Metric.ball, Real.dist_eq]\n                          <;>\n                          norm_num <;>\n                          linarith\n                        })\n                    })\n                exact hтВБтВЙ\n              have hтВВтВА : Filter.Tendsto (fun x : тДЭ => Real.sinh x / x) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := hтВВ\n              have hтВВтВБ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) := hтВБтВЗ\n              have hтВВтВВ : Filter.Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => Real.sinh (r / k) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) :=\n                hтВВтВА.comp hтВВтВБ\n              simpa [Function.comp] using hтВВтВВ\n            simpa using hтВБтВЖ\n          exact hтВИ\n        exact hтВЕ\n    exact hтВГ\n  \n  -- Use the above result to prove the main theorem\n  have hтВВ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => k * Real.sinh (r / k)) atTop (ЁЭУЭ r) := by\n    have hтВГ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (Real.sinh (r / k)) / (r / k)) (ЁЭУЭ[тЙа] 0) (ЁЭУЭ 1) := hтВБ\n    have hтВД : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => k * Real.sinh (r / k)) atTop (ЁЭУЭ r) := by\n      -- Use the fact that as k тЖТ тИЮ, r/k тЖТ 0 to relate to the previous limit\n      have hтВЕ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) atTop (ЁЭУЭ 0) := by\n        have hтВЖ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r / k : тДЭ)) atTop (ЁЭУЭ 0) := by\n          have hтВЗ : Tendsto (fun k : тДЭ => (r : тДЭ) / k) atTop (ЁЭУЭ 0) := by\n            convert tendsto_const_nhds.div_atTop tendsto_id using 1\n            <;> simp [div_eq_mul_inv]\n            <;> field_simp",
